# Chrome Guard

Chrome Guard is a lightweight desktop utility that launches Google Chrome using a low-latency profile and continuously monitors how Chrome uses your system resources. It provides a simple Tkinter desktop UI that displays real-time CPU usage, identifies heavy Chrome subprocesses, and sends alerts when sustained spikes occur.

## Features

* Launch Chrome with an optimized low-latency profile
* Real-time total CPU usage from all Chrome processes
* Identify the single Chrome subprocess using the most CPU
* Estimate per-tab CPU contribution through the Chrome DevTools Protocol
* Clean Tkinter UI for meters, tab list, alerts, and URL launching
* Alerts for sustained CPU spikes caused by specific Chrome components
* Open URLs directly from the app without needing the CLI

