## Installation

### Create a virtual environment

python3 -m venv .venv

### Activate it

source .venv/bin/activate

### Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

## Running Chrome Guard

### Launch the full desktop UI

python3 scripts/run_gui.py

### Run the monitor alone (logs only, no UI)

python3 scripts/run_monitor_only.py

## Configuration

Environment variables can override defaults in config.py:

CHROME_GUARD_CHROME_PATH
CHROME_GUARD_CPU_TOTAL
CHROME_GUARD_CPU_SINGLE
CHROME_GUARD_POLL_INTERVAL
CHROME_GUARD_SUSTAINED_HITS

These are optional. The program runs out-of-the-box using sensible defaults.

## Platform Notes

* Works on macOS and Linux
* Uses remote debugging on port 9222 for per-tab metrics
* Requires Chrome or Chromium installed locally
